article.headline: Savannah St. 57, S. Carolina St. 53
article.story: SAVANNAH, Ga. -- Tracy Rankins scored 19 points to lead Savannah State to a 57-53 win over South Carolina State on Wednesday night. The Tigers (9-8) have won nine of their 10 home games this season. South Carolina State (6-8) led by as many as six points in the first half, but Savannah State rallied to lead 32-29 at the break. After the Tigers built a nine-point lead at 49-40, the Bulldogs cut the margin to four points with 3:32 left. Jason Johnson made a layup with 10 seconds left to pull South Carolina State within three at 56-53, but missed his subsequent free throw. Two seconds later, Chris Linton hit the first of two free-throw attempts to seal the win for the Tigers. Anthony Jones and Jovonni Shuler added 11 points apiece for Savannah State. Johnson paced the Bulldogs with 17 points on 7-of-8 shooting and Jason Flagler added 10 points.
